On Escalation Ticket # 00438405 the new comment has been added: Iuri Tovcaci:

@WaitingOnEngineer The EPP agent code gets the client event time using directly a Windows API (GetSystemTime), without any interpretation. In this case, it would be helpful to have the Windows Event Viewer logs (eventvwr.msc) for "Windows Logs -> System" for the specified date ranges. Unsuccessful synchronization with either RTC or NTP servers might cause an incorrect UTC time and this should be logged by the OS itself.

